# Flight Academy CODEOWNERS
#
# Order matters — the LAST matching pattern wins per file.
# Patterns use a syntax similar to .gitignore. Leading slash means repo-root only.
#
# Updating this file requires existing code owners to approve (the rule applies
# recursively to itself). See:
# https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Default — everything not otherwise matched
*                                   @ICreateThunder

# Governance, legal, policy — extra explicit (even though * covers them)
/LICENSE                            @ICreateThunder
/SECURITY.md                        @ICreateThunder
/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md                 @ICreateThunder
/GOVERNANCE.md                      @ICreateThunder
/CONTRIBUTING.md                    @ICreateThunder
/CODEOWNERS                         @ICreateThunder
/.github/CODEOWNERS                 @ICreateThunder

# CI, automation, security-sensitive workflows
/.github/                           @ICreateThunder

# Architectural decisions and threat model
/docs/architecture/                 @ICreateThunder
/docs/security/                     @ICreateThunder

# Future: as the maintainer team grows, sensitive paths will gain specific reviewers.
# Indicative shape (commented; uncomment + populate when teams exist):
#
# /crates/fa-auth/                  @ICreateThunder @flight-academy-uk/security
# /crates/fa-store/                 @ICreateThunder @flight-academy-uk/security
# /crates/fa-db/migrations/         @ICreateThunder @flight-academy-uk/db
# /deploy/                          @ICreateThunder @flight-academy-uk/infra
